annotation.TEXT: I remember how I crashed into the side of this Chuck last time. That's not happening again.
Credit goes to hohum on the Exploding Rabbit forums for finding that glitch! (And you don't even need the "All Ground is Bricks" cheat turned on for that glitch to occur!)
Up next is Howater Cave. What exactly does "Howater" mean, anyway? Just wondering.
Hard demo count: 2
!ush!
...Assuming I can make him respawn...
Oh, and is "hyper avoid" a reference to the Yoshi n Berry level from EVW?
I'm going to be sure not to get Blargged here this time.
Whoa! Almost crashed into that Pokey.
I somehow stomped that troll head at a weird angle.
Goal tape average so far: Hard: 120 / 3 = 40 stars each. Overall: 260 / 7 = 37.143 stars each.
Yeah, there's no chance of reaching the second pair of munchers during the first T-switch's effect. You need the second T-switch.
Ah, I'm more pleased with my timing there than the last time I cleared this level. Unfortunately, my 1-up got stuck in the ceiling again. D'oh.
...Or not, because I screwed it up and my shell despawned. Well, whatever. I think that big spring deserves to be bounced on anyway.
Whoa! Why'd the Thwomp appear that time? Good thing my triangle shell took care of it! Also, I'm not letting that spike hit me this time!
Also, I hope I can take out the boss without getting hit! Well, I succeeded in doing that last time, so I should be able to this time, right?
Yep.
Alright, it's boss time!
BGM: Touhou 8 - Stage 3 - Nostalgic Blood of the East ~ Old World
Whoa. I briefly considered trying to slide-kill that Triangley, but it would've been a dangerously tight fit. Besides, the kicked triangle shell here gets rid of him one piece at a time.
Wow, that was certainly an interesting dodge!
Hmm... Maybe I can skip having to use the big spring with a shell jump...
Cool, I didn't barf it this time.
Ed ora, gioco bonus velocità ridicola.
Meh. Useless power up.
Okay, back to ludicrous speed now.
Well, let's-a-go!
Blah, blah, equilateral, isosceles, scalene, right, hypotenuse, Pythagoras, blah, blah.
I didn't forget about the hidden Thwomps!
Yeah, yeah. I know my time's low. I'm close to the end.
Shut up, clock! I'm going just about as fast as I can!

Once again, I'm pretty sure I want to speedrun the level. Oh, and that's funny how my reserve mushroom's got the dorky smile that the "Chilly Shroom" later on has. But, my reserve mushroom doesn't make me "trippy".
No one ever answered this when I asked last time: Since that elevator's on layer 2, does that mean the cloudy background is on layer 3?
I wonder why it's hard to detach from underwater slopes while you're carrying something?
Honestly, I got really lucky back there that I avoided getting tackled by the Chucks just after jumping over that spike!
Hmm... Now, I could save Triangle Fortress and White Switch Palace for another episode, but I kind of want to get this whole thing done now. So, here we go!
Okay, now to aim for a high goal tape value this time, I'm going to enlist the help of this shell-less koopa here.
Tush! Ooh, T-switch jump again!
Oh, what?! I actually got hit by that last spike while riding the raft normally? That's just dumb!
Whoa, gotta be careful. With the off screen ceiling in effect and the fact that one hit kills, jumping over that high up spike is really dangerous!
BOING!
Alright, so I'm gonna wait on the White Switch Palace for now, which means The Chilly Shroom is next!
Alright, time to get "trippy"!
(Of course, I know it's not actually the mushroom power up itself in this level that makes me "trippy". It's actually the teleport tiles underneath it that send me into the "trippy" area.)
What the heck just happened there? SMIR (Slow-motion instant replay) time!
Yes, that troll head almost fell on me there, which would've definitely qualified as a trollish move! But, I somehow avoided it.
Okay, now that I've completed every level on Hard, can I finally open the fridge or destroy the table in Luigis House?
Okay, I'm going to have to do the slow-motion instant replay thing for that one!
And we return to normalcy.
D'oh! I did crash into that koopa... Also, looks like taking a hit removes my reserve item in addition to killing me.
Hello, and welcome back to Mario's Search For His Hat! So, will I be playing the White Switch Palace now? Or will I wait on that until after I've played all the other levels? Let's find out...
Whoa. Good thing I reacted fast enough, or I would've been trolled there!
Hah. Dodged the triangle power up this time.
And now, ludicrous speed me getting back to where I was.
Yeah, I could try shell jumping again with this shell, but I've already made the decision to do this part the normal way.
Go, my white blocks, and do absolutely nothing here! (Maybe they're going over to where Google's HQ is to knock some sense into those losers there?)
Nuts. I was trying to avoid collecting that. Yeah, since power ups are something I kind of want to avoid now, that seemingly well-meaning triangle is now technically against me too.
I see you this time, spike.
At least Hard mode doesn't actually make these evil mushrooms any harder, because they already insta-kill me!

Actually, after I finished putting together this movie last night, I got a vote for someone to make the voter an avatar with both Luigi and Marisa in it, and a vote to play the White Switch Palace now. So, that means there's actually 3 votes for the WSP, but that doesn't affect the outcome here at all.
Let's try that again, with less ramming into the back of koopas this time.
Goal tape average: Hard: 148 / 4 = 37 stars each. Overall: 288 / 8 = 36 stars each.
Whoops, I need to take the top route now.

And, that's it... Except it's not. I still have the White Switch Palace to play! Unfortunately, I did not see any differences in any of the levels at all whether the WSP was activated or not. Does the White Switch Palace even have any effect anywhere in this hack?
Did that bullet behind me just vanish? Who knows. Also, I'm not bothering with midpoint, because it would only hinder me right now.
Demo count: FTW
Let's see... Did I keep that hidden Thwomp from spawning again?
Come on, can't I make this jump?
I'm still going for all of the golden troll faces, of course.
◢ush!
Oh, god. I hope I'll have enough time to take out the boss!
Tush! Whoa, I got dangerously close to the munchers as I was tushing that T-switch.
Whoa! That was close!
Bonus game average: Hard: 8 / 1 = 8 1-ups each. Overall: 13 / 2 = 6.5 1-ups each.

It's that glitch where a shell that hits the top of Pokey's/Triangley's head at just the right angle will cause a knocked-off head to appear, but won't actually have knocked the head off the body! Also, I'm lucky I didn't land on Triangley's head after that happened!
I think at this point, I'm probably better off being small, unless there's another Yoshi head that requires me to break a turn block with a spin jump to reach...

Dang, doesn't look like it. Stupid indestructible things... Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through Mario's Search For His Hat! Join me next time, when I play through another of Neidave's hacks!
Got him! I do like how the level ends the instant you land the last hit, so you don't have to worry about the timer or any leftover triangles killing you during the boss's death animation.
Hard demo count: 1
28? What is this garbage? I did better last time when I was just running and jumping from the ground. (Of course, I was big here last time, which helped.)
